    "The model must sample an observation x from the training set during the denoising operation, which subsequently generates a corresponding corrupted x 0 according to the corruption process P( x 0 |x).",
    "Then, as shown in Fig. 23 [107], x 0 is encoded to provide a hidden representation h for the data.2.",
    "GAN: Using Generative Adversarial Networks, it is possible to train such detailed models to mimic a genuine distribution.",
    "By defining the problem as a supervised learning problem with two sub-models-the generator model we train to generate new examples and the discriminator model that attempts to classify examples as either real (from the domain) or fake (generated)-generative adversarial networks are a creative way to train a generative model [19, 54].",
    "In other words, the generator model is used to generate new credible examples from the problem domain."
